Description:
[recto] St. John Baptist Preaching. Warburg Photo Collection under Saints: St. John Baptist. 
St John pointing to Christ: Ph. Galle after M. van Heemskerck, Leyden Print Room (Hollstein, VII, 190-192; Ghirlandaio, Florence S. Maria Novella, Sermon with Christ present, but St. John not pointing to him, but this composition may have been known to Bruegel (Listeners in circle around St. John); A. Pisano, Florence Baptistery Door, St. John pointing to Christ; Schongauer, St. John pointing to Christ (St. George), in Colmar; Follower of Bouts, St. John pointing to Christ, Berlin Mus.
 Virgil Solis (B. IX, 252.41) pointing to Christ, not preaching, Evang. Johannes I; Cornelis Massys (B.IX, 177,28) pointing to Christ signed in monogram & dated 1550. 
Preaching without Christ.
Duccio, Baptist preaching in Christ's presence; Budapest; Bles, Vienna; Jan Swart, Munich, N° 741, with Orientals; Manner of Lucas Gassel (?)[sic], Baptism in foreground preaching in background;  Art Dealer W. Schlayer, Madrid (?)[sic] as by Patinir, Photo Netherl. Art Inst. N° 7563; 
[verso] Copy after Bruegel, with the man having his fortune told absent Sotheby's 27-3-74, signed, panel 47 x 653/4inc. Attr. to Brunswick Monogramist, St. John Preaching (with Bruegel motifs, Sale Christie's, Dec. 8, 1972, and Christie's, 5 Dec. 1969, N° 141; P.B.II after P.B.I, with man having fortune told, Valenciennes Mus. cat. 1931, N° 38, canvas 105 x 160 cm; Herri met de Bles, Baptist Preaching (Baptism in background), Christie 17-7-64, lot 95; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. rather by Lucas Gassel'; P. Balten, based on Bruegel, 38 3/4 x 48 3/4 in.; Andrea del Sarto (fresco) in Chiostro dello Scalzo and chalk drawing connected with this in Uffizi. After Bruegel: B[uda]pest: Lier Mus. (Coll. Caroly) signed & dated P. BRVEGHEL 1604 Man having fortune told absent, 106 x 169 cm; Antw.Mus. 'falsely (?)[sic] signed': P. BREVGEL F', panel 105,4 x 167 cm; Munich, Pinakothek (Photo Coll. Haufstängl) '383', Jan Brueghel d.\*A. with man having fortune told.[scan]
